<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-19T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-19T17:00:00-05:00" n="607" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d607">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">693.113 (Manchuria) Petroleum/56:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-19T17:00:00-05:00">April 19, 1934—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>52. Peiping’s telegram No. 175, April 17, 1 p.m.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>Department believes that it would be desirable that you make
                                representations at the Foreign Office with a view to reinforcing oil
                                companies’ representations at Dairen. (See page 3, Dairen’s
                                despatch, March 3, 1934, to Peiping.<note n="90" xml:id="d607fn90">Not printed.</note>) It leaves to your discretion whether the
                                representations should be made formally or along the lines of
                                Department’s telegrams No. 89, October 6, 5 p.m.,<note n="91" xml:id="d607fn91"><ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_125"><hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941,
                                        vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 125</ref>.</note> and
                                No. 97, October 14, 4 p.m.<note n="92" xml:id="d607fn92"><ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_126"><hi rend="italic">Ibid</hi>.,
                                        p. 126</ref>.</note></item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>Assuming that your British colleague is prepared to take similar
                                action (Department’s 50, April 17, 3 p.m.<note n="90" xml:id="d607fn93">Not printed.</note>), please notify him of the
                                above.</item>
                        </list>
                        <p>Repeat to Peiping as Dep[artmen]t’s 118.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>